    • Method Detail

      • setMessageCallback

        public void setMessageCallback(netscape.javascript.JSObject callback)
        Sets the JavaScript callback to invoke when a message is received from the launched app. The callback should be a function that accepts a single string parameter (the received message).

      • sendMessage

        public boolean sendMessage(String message)
        Attempts to send a message to the launched app.
        Returns:
        true if we succeeded in sending the message, false if the launched app has not (yet) established a connection to Getdown, or the send failed.
